        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): preserve corrupt-header transcripts",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Prevent `prepareSessionManagerForRun` from clearing an existing session transcript when the on-disk header is unreadable.\r\n- Surface the corrupt-header condition instead, preserving the original transcript bytes for recovery/inspection.\r\n- Add a regression test that writes a malformed first JSONL line plus a persisted user message and proves the file is unchanged after the guarded path rejects.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\n\r\nCloses #89037.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: resuming a session whose first JSONL header line is corrupted could reach the no-assistant reset path and truncate the transcript.\r\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout at current `origin/main` with the real filesystem-backed `prepareSessionManagerForRun` helper and a temp JSONL transcript file.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `PNPM_CONFIG_OFFLINE=true corepack pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`.\r\n- Evidence after fix: the new regression passes and asserts the original malformed transcript string remains byte-for-byte unchanged after the helper rejects.\r\n- Observed result after fix: the helper throws `Refusing to reset session transcript with unreadable header` before `fs.writeFile(..., \"\")` can run.\r\n- What was not tested: a live production resume against a real user transcript was not performed.\r\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: I avoided using private/local user session transcripts; the regression uses a disposable temp transcript with the same destructive file operation path.\r\n- Before evidence: the existing no-assistant branch unconditionally called `fs.writeFile(params.sessionFile, \"\", \"utf-8\")` for any `hadSessionFile && header && !hasAssistant` state.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n\r\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --write --threads=1 src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.test.ts`\r\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_OFFLINE=true corepack pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.test.ts -- --reporter=dot` passed 1 Vitest shard / 3 tests.\r\n- `git diff --check -- src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-manager-init.test.ts` passed.\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n\r\n- Did user-visible behavior change? Yes, corrupt session-header resumes now fail before destructive reset instead of silently wiping the file.\r\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? No.\r\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No.\r\n- Highest-risk area: preserving the existing first-run session-manager workaround. The guard only reads and validates the existing first nonblank line before the reset; valid pre-created session headers still follow the old reset path.\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\n\r\nReady for review. No bot or reviewer comments have been addressed yet.",
